# .leak-patterns.local.example — TEMPLATE for the local pre-push leak scanner.
#
# Copy this file to `.leak-patterns.local` (gitignored) and fill in patterns
# that must NEVER appear in a public commit:
#
#   cp .leak-patterns.local.example .leak-patterns.local
#   $EDITOR .leak-patterns.local
#
# Format: one extended-regex pattern per line. Lines starting with # are
# comments. scripts/check-leaks.sh greps the repo tree with `grep -Eifn`
# against this file.
#
# Suggested categories:

# --- Org / product / internal codenames ----------------------------------
# YourOrgName
# YourProductName
# YourInternalCodename

# --- Hosts ---------------------------------------------------------------
# your-org\.atlassian\.net
# api\.your-product\.com

# --- VPS / infra IPs -----------------------------------------------------
# 10\.0\.0\.1
# /home/your-vps-user/

# --- User-specific paths ------------------------------------------------
# /Users/your-mac-user/

# --- Token formats (these are universal — already covered by sanitize.sed,
#     listed here for the pre-push double-check) -----------------------------
ATATT3xFfGF0[A-Za-z0-9_=-]{8,}
figd_[A-Za-z0-9_-]{8,}
gho_[A-Za-z0-9]{8,}
sk-[A-Za-z0-9]{20,}
AKIA[A-Z0-9]{16}
